{
  "texts": [
    "The results are organized in two subsections.",
    "The initial subsection focuses on the CD case study, where we assess the RL algorithm's effectiveness when the reward structure includes diversity alongside execution time, and contrast these results against scenarios where the reward is solely based on execution time.",
    "The subsequent subsection examines the application of the RL approach to the 6-DOF case study, employing the same comparative analysis between reward structures that either do or do not incorporate diversity.In the implementation of the RL component of this study, we utilized the Stable Baselines3 library [119], a popular framework designed to facilitate the development and comparison of RL algorithms.",
    "Stable Baselines3, building upon its predecessor Stable Baselines (which itself extends OpenAI Baselines), offers a set of PyTorch-based RL implementations.",
    "The library's straightforward interface and extensive documentation have streamlined the process of algorithm selection and experimentation, enabling a more efficient exploration of the RL solution space."
  ]
}